channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Snap U.K. election sends crypto industry scrambling to court Labour allies
item.description: The crypto lobby has been preparing for a changing of the political guard.

item.title: Porsche, VW and other European carmakers fall following reports of 'dieselgate' lawsuits in Britain
item.description: The "dieselgate" emissions scandal refers to reports that first surfaced in 2015 Volkswagen had been caught cheating on emissions tests in the U.S.

item.title: Oracle’s cloud AI deals excite investors, but do they have long-term potential?
Why Russia, China and Big Tech all use fake female online profiles to get clicks
item.description: The human brain remains surprisingly easy to hack thanks in part to age-old gender stereotypes that have migrated from the real world to the virtual.

item.title: European Union announces higher tariffs of up to 38% on Chinese EVs
item.description: The European Union on Wednesday said it would slap higher tariffs on Chinese electric vehicle imports.

item.title: Here's why Joey Chestnut has been banned from famed hot-dog eating contest
EV adoption has another problem
item.description: In late May, copper hit a record high of nearly $5.20 a pound.

item.title: Wednesday's analyst calls: Street reacts to Oracle AI announcements, Goldman downgrades shoe stock
item.description: A software giant and a shoe stock were among the stocks being talked about on Wall Street.

item.title: Elon Musk drops suit against OpenAI’s Sam Altman in latest chapter of AI saga
Elizabeth Holmes watches from a Texas prison as appeal of her Theranos fraud conviction begins in federal court
item.description: The hearing held in the San Francisco appeals court came nearly 2 1/2 years after a jury convicted Holmes for orchestrating a blood-testing scam that became a parable about greed and hubris in Silicon Valley.

item.title: More than $1 billion in EV tax credits issued upfront to buyers, Treasury and IRS say
item.description: Federal officials said the Biden administration hit a key milestone in its push to make it easier for consumers to buy an electric vehicle.

item.title: Apple adds $215B in market cap as stock leads S&P 500 for first time in years
California fast-tracks bill to make marketplaces like eBay collect bank account and tax ID numbers from high-volume online sellers
item.description: The idea is that thieves will be less likely to resell stolen merchandise if authorities can track them down.

item.title: Big Oil given stark warning as peak crude and a major supply surplus expected by 2030
item.description: The IEA on Wednesday said a U.S.-led surge in global oil production is expected to outstrip demand growth between now and the end of the decade.
